rowse avatar library\tProduct niche, target demographic\tShortlist 5-10 suitable avatars\t15 min 3\tWrite ad scripts\tProduct features, pain points, CTAs\t3-5 script variations (30-45 sec each)\t30 min 4\tGenerate first video\tScript, avatar selection, voice tone\tMP4 video file ready\t2 min 5\tReview & iterate\tFeedback on pacing, clarity, emotion\tRefined video version\t15 min 6\tAdd B-roll & music\tBrand assets, stock footage, audio\tPolished final video\t10 min 7\tExport & optimize\tPlatform specs (FB/IG/TikTok)\tPlatform-specific formats\t5 min 8\tUpload to ad platforms\tAd account access, campaign structure\tLive ad campaign\t20 min 9\tMonitor & scale\tPerformance data\tNew video variations\tOngoing Total Setup Time: 1.5-2 hours | Ongoing: 30-45 min per video batch For ZEELY.AI: Step\tAction\tExpected Input\tExpected Output\tTime 1\tDownload app or visit site\tEmail, password, business type\tAccount created\t3 min 2\tConnect store (optional)\tShopify URL or manual product entry\tProduct catalog synced\t5 min 3\tAdd first product\tProduct URL or manual details\tAI-extracted product data\t2 min 4\tSelect template\tCampaign objective, audience type\tTemplate preview loaded\t3 min 5\tGenerate static ads\tClick \"Generate\"\t5-10 static ad variations\t3 min 6\tCreate video ad\tSelect avatar, AI generates script\tUGC-style video ad\t7 min 7\tReview & edit\tMinor tweaks to copy/visuals\tFinal ad creatives\t5 min 8\tSet up campaign\tBudget, targeting, duration\tCampaign draft ready\t5 min 9\tLaunch ads\tApprove and go live\tActive campaigns on FB/IG\t2 min 10\tMonitor AI dashboard\tCheck daily\tPerformance reports, AI recommendations\t5 min/day Total Setup Time: 30-40 minutes | Ongoing: 5-10 min/day for monitoring 💡 MONETIZATION & CONVERSION OPTIMIZATION TACTICS For ARCADS.AI Users: Testing Framework: Create 10 videos with same script, different avatars - test which converts best Localization Play: Use multi-language feature to expand to international markets Hook Variations: Generate 5 videos with different opening hooks, same core message Emotion Testing: Test different emotional tones (excited vs calm vs urgent) Platform Optimization: Create separate videos optimized for TikTok vs Instagram vs Facebook A/B Testing: Run avatar A vs avatar B to same audience, double down on winner For ZEELY.AI Users: Bulk Template Testing: Generate 20+ static ads at once, let AI identify top performers Full Funnel Approach: Create awareness (video) + retargeting (static) ad sequences Automated Scaling: Let AI increase budget on winning campaigns automatically Cross-Platform Strategy: Launch simultaneously on FB, IG, and Google for data Product Testing: Add multiple products, see which AI-generated ads perform best CTA Optimization: Use AI recommendations to test different calls-to-action 📚 KNOWLEDGE BASE SUMMARY Document Purpose: Compare Arcads.ai vs Zeely.ai for AI-powered ad creation Key Findings: Arcads.ai = Premium UGC video specialist ($110-220/month, 1,000+ avatars, video-only) Zeely.ai = All-in-one affordable solution ($30-80/month, 30+ avatars, video + static + campaigns) Quality vs Cost trade-off: Arcads higher quality but 3-4x more expensive Use case clarity: Arcads for pros/agencies, Zeely for startups/small businesses Support concerns: Both have mixed reviews, Zeely has more red flags on customer service Decision Matrix: Budget <$500/month → Zeely Budget >$1,000/month → Arcads Need static ads → Zeely Need campaign management → Zeely Need best avatars → Arcads Need video only → Arcads 🔗 OFFICIAL RESOURCES Arcads.ai: https://arcads.ai Zeely.ai: https://zeely.ai Arcads Reviews: Trustpilot Zeely Reviews: Trustpilot Detailed Arcads Review: MarketerMilk Zeely Pricing: Official Pricing Page Bottom Line: If you're bootstrapping an e-commerce store or dropshipping business, start with Zeely.ai at $29.95/month for the complete package. If you're scaling with a serious ad budget ($5K+/month) and need Hollywood-quality UGC videos, invest in Arcads.ai. Don't let shiny features distract you - pick based on your current revenue, not aspirational goals. Want me to create implementation workflows, ad copy templates, or ROI tracking spreadsheets for either platform? yes do all for both. for the shopify store we are workgin on with the print on demand product suite 🚀 COMPLETE IMPLEMENTATION PACKAGE: ARCADS.AI + ZEELY.AI FOR SHOPIFY PRINT-ON-DEMAND Alright, let's build you a battle-tested system for your Shopify POD store. I'm giving you everything - workflows, ad copy templates, ROI trackers, and tactical playbooks for both platforms. 📋 TABLE OF CONTENTS Shopify POD Store Setup & Integration Arcads.ai Complete Implementation Workflow Zeely.ai Complete Implementation Workflow Ad Copy Templates (50+ Variations) ROI Tracking Spreadsheets & Formulas Print-on-Demand Specific Strategies Campaign Launch Checklists Optimization Playbooks 1️⃣ SHOPIFY POD STORE SETUP & INTEGRATION CHECKLIST Pre-Launch Requirements (Complete These First) Task\tAction Steps\tExpected Output\tStatus Store Setup\t1. Domain configured 2. Theme installed & customized 3. Logo & branding assets ready 4. Legal pages (Privacy, Terms, Refund)\tFully functional Shopify store\t☐ POD Products\t1. Select niche (apparel, mugs, posters, etc.) 2. Upload designs to POD supplier 3. Create product listings with mockups 4. Set pricing (Cost + 40-60% markup)\t5-10 products live on store\t☐ Product Photography\t1. High-res mockups from POD supplier 2. Lifestyle images (3-5 per product) 3. Detail shots showing print quality 4. Size/fit guide images\tImage library organized in Google Drive\t☐ Facebook Business Setup\t1. Create Facebook Business Manager 2. Add Ad Account 3. Install Facebook Pixel on Shopify 4. Verify domain 5. Create Facebook Page & Instagram\tPixel tracking, accounts verified\t☐ Payment Processing\t1. Enable Shopify Payments or Stripe 2. Set up PayPal 3. Test checkout flow 4. Configure tax settings\tPayment processing active\t☐ Product Data Export\t1. Export product CSV from Shopify 2. Prepare product URLs for AI tools 3. Write 3-5 key benefits per product 4. List target customer demographics\tProduct data sheet completed\t☐ 2️⃣ ARCADS.AI COMPLETE IMPLEMENTATION WORKFLOW 🎯 30-DAY ARCADS IMPLEMENTATION ROADMAP FOR POD WEEK 1: Foundation & First Videos Using Tool | Think The user wants comprehensive implementation workflows for both Arcads.ai and Zeely.ai specifically for their Shopify print-on-demand store. I should create detailed, tactical SOPs with: 1. Step-by-step workflows with exact timing 2. Ad copy templates specifically for POD products 3. ROI tracking spreadsheets with formulas 4. Print-on-demand specific strategies (different from general e-commerce) 5. Campaign checklists and optimization playbooks For POD specifically, I need to consider: - Visual-first products (designs are the hero) - Emotional connection to designs - Gift-giving occasions - Niche targeting (specific communities/interests) - Lower AOV typically ($25-50) - Longer fulfillment times - Custom/personalized angle I'll create actionable templates and spreadsheets that they can actually use. View Day\tTask\tClick-by-Click Steps\tExpected Input\tExpected Output\tTime Day 1\tAccount Setup\t1. Go to arcads.ai 2. Click \"Get Started\" 3. Enter email & create password 4. Select \"Starter\" plan ($110/month) 5. Enter payment details 6. Verify email 7. Complete onboarding survey (select \"E-commerce\")\tBusiness email, credit card, company name\tActive Arcads account with 10 video credits\t15 min Day 2\tAvatar Research\t1. Click \"Avatars\" in sidebar 2. Filter by: Gender, Age (25-45 for POD), Ethnicity (diverse) 3. Watch preview clips of 20+ avatars 4. Bookmark 10 avatars that match your brand vibe 5. Screenshot your favorites for reference\tYour brand personality (casual/professional/edgy)\tShortlist of 10 avatars with IDs saved\t45 min Day 3\tScript Writing (Product 1)\t1. Open Google Doc template (below) 2. Fill in: Product name, key benefit, pain point, CTA 3. Write 3 hook variations (first 3 seconds) 4. Write 3 body variations (problem/solution) 5. Write 3 CTA variations 6. Keep total under 45 seconds when spoken 7. Read aloud to test pacing\tProduct 1 details, target audience info\t9 script variations (3×3×3 matrix)\t90 min Day 4\tFirst Video Batch\t1. Log into Arcads 2. Click \"Create New Video\" 3. Paste Script Version 1 4. Select Avatar #1 from your shortlist 5. Choose voice tone: \"Friendly & Conversational\" 6. Click \"Generate\" 7. Wait 2 minutes 8. Repeat for Scripts 2-3 with different avatars 9. Download all 3 videos\t3 scripts, 3 avatar selections\t3 complete video ads (MP4 format)\t30 min Day 5\tVideo Review & Feedback\t1. Watch each video 3 times 2. Check: Lip sync quality, pacing, authenticity 3. Share with 3 team members or friends 4. Collect feedback in shared Google Sheet 5. Identify: Best avatar, best script hook, areas to improve\t3 videos to review\tRanked list (best to worst) + improvement notes\t60 min Day 6-7\tBatch Production\t1. Take winning script + avatar combo 2. Create 5 variations changing only the hook 3. Generate all 5 videos 4. Add B-roll (product shots) using Arcads editor 5. Add background music (upbeat for POD) 6. Export in formats: 1:1 (IG/FB), 9:16 (Stories/Reels), 16:9 (YouTube)\tWinning base script, 5 hook variations\t15 final videos (5 scripts × 3 formats)\t3 hours WEEK 2: Campaign Setup & Launch Day\tTask\tClick-by-Click Steps\tExpected Input\tExpected Output\tTime Day 8\tFacebook Ads Manager Setup\t1. Go to business.facebook.com 2. Click \"Ads Manager\" 3. Click green \"+ Create\" button 4. Select objective: \"Sales\" 5. Name campaign: \"POD_Arcads_Test_[ProductName]\" 6. Budget: $20/day to start 7. Click \"Continue\"\tFacebook Business Manager access\tCampaign shell created\t20 min Day 9\tAudience Creation\t1. In Ad Set level, click \"Create New Audience\" 2. Location: USA (or your target country) 3. Age: 25-55 4. Gender: All (or product-specific) 5. Detailed Targeting: Add 10 interests related to your POD niche 6. Example for funny shirts: \"Comedy\", \"Memes\", \"SNL\" 7. Audience size target: 1-5 million 8. Save audience as \"POD_Core_[NicheName]\"\tPOD niche details, customer avatar\t3 saved audiences for testing\t30 min Day 10\tAd Upload (Video 1)\t1. In Ads level, click \"+ Create Ad\" 2. Select \"Single video\" 3. Upload best Arcads video (1:1 format) 4. Primary text: Use template below (50-75 words) 5. Headline: 5 words max, benefit-focused 6. Description: CTA with urgency 7. Add \"Shop Now\" CTA button 8. Destination: Product page URL 9. Preview on all placements\tVideo file, ad copy, product URL\tAd #1 ready to publish\t20 min Day 11\tLaunch 3 Ad Variations\t1. Duplicate Ad #1 twice 2. Ad #2: Swap video with different hook 3. Ad #3: Swap video with different avatar 4. Keep audience + budget same across all 3 5. Click \"Publish\" on campaign 6. Confirm $20/day spend\t3 video files, 1 audience, 1 ad copy\t3 ads live, spending $20/day\t30 min Day 12-14\tMonitor & Collect Data\t1. Check Ads Manager daily at 9am 2. Record: Impressions, CPM, CTR, CPC, Purchases 3. Don't change anything for 3 days (learning phase) 4. Wait for 50+ clicks before optimizing 5. Watch for \"Learning\" to become \"Active\"\tDaily check-ins\t3 days of performance data\t15 min/day WEEK 3: Optimization & Scaling Day\tTask\tClick-by-Click Steps\tExpected Input\tExpected Output\tTime Day 15\tPerformance Analysis\t1. Open Facebook Ads Manager 2. Click \"Columns\" → \"Customize Columns\" 3. Add: CTR, CPC, ROAS, Purchases, Add to Cart 4. Sort ads by CTR (highest to lowest) 5. Identify winner: CTR >1.5% and CPC <$1.50 6. Export report to Google Sheets\tFacebook Ads data\tWinner identified, data exported\t30 min Day 16\tKill Losers\t1. Turn off ads with CTR <1% and 0 purchases 2. Keep winner running at $20/day 3. Create 2 new variations of winner (change copy only) 4. Launch new variations at $15/day each\tWinner ad data\t1 winning ad + 2 new tests live\t20 min Day 17\tCreate Product 2 Videos\t1. Go back to Arcads 2. Use winning avatar from Product 1 3. Write new scripts for Product 2 (3 variations) 4. Generate 3 videos using proven avatar 5. Add B-roll for Product 2 6. Export in all formats\tProduct 2 details, winning avatar\t9 videos for Product 2 (3 scripts × 3 formats)\t2 hours Day 18-21\tScale Winner\t1. If winning ad has ROAS >2.0 after 3 days 2. Increase budget by 20% daily (Day 18: $24, Day 19: $29, Day 20: $35) 3. Duplicate winning ad set to new audience 4. Launch lookalike audience (1% of website visitors) 5. Keep original ad running\tWinning ad with ROAS >2.0\tScaled to $35/day + new audience test\t30 min/day WEEK 4: Expand & Automate Day\tTask\tClick-by-Click Steps\tExpected Input\tExpected Output\tTime Day 22-24\tProduct 2 Launch\t1. Repeat Days 8-11 for Product 2 2. Use proven ad structure from Product 1 3. Launch with $20/day budget 4. Test on same winning audience\tProduct 2 videos, proven structure\tProduct 2 ads live\t2 hours Day 25-27\tRetargeting Campaign\t1. Create custom audience: \"Website visitors, 14 days\" 2. Create new campaign: \"POD_Retargeting\" 3. Use UGC videos showing social proof 4. Ad copy: \"Still thinking about [Product]? Get 10% off today!\" 5. Budget: $10/day 6. Exclude: Purchasers\tWebsite traffic (min 100 visitors)\tRetargeting campaign live\t45 min Day 28-30\tBatch Month 2 Content\t1. Generate 20 new videos for Month 2 2. Mix: 5 videos per top 4 products 3. Test new avatars (expand beyond winner) 4. Test seasonal hooks (holidays, events) 5. Download and organize in folder\tProducts 1-4 data, new hooks\t60 videos ready for Month 2 rotation\t4 hours 📝 ARCADS SCRIPT TEMPLATES FOR PRINT-ON-DEMAND Template 1: Problem-Solution (Funny/Novelty POD) Copy [Hook - 3 seconds] \"Tired of boring [shirts/mugs/gifts] that nobody laughs at?\" [Problem - 8 seconds] \"Everyone's giving the same generic gifts from the mall. You want something that actually gets a reaction.\" [Solution - 10 seconds] \"That's why we created [Product Name] - the [shirt/mug/poster] that finally says what everyone's thinking. It's [funny/sarcastic/relatable] and gets compliments every time.\" [Social Proof - 8 seconds] \"Over 5,000 customers have made their friends laugh with this design.\" [CTA - 6 seconds] \"Click the link to grab yours before we sell out. Free shipping over $35!\" [Urgency - 3 seconds] \"Limited stock - order yours now!\" Variables to Test: Avatar: Comedic female vs relatable male Tone: Sarcastic vs enthusiastic Hook: Question vs statement CTA: \"Order now\" vs \"Grab yours\" vs \"Shop the collection\" Template 2: Identity/Pride (Niche Community POD) Copy [Hook - 3 seconds] \"If you're a [dog mom/nurse/teacher/veteran], this is for you.\" [Identity - 8 seconds] \"Being a [identity] isn't just what you do - it's who you are. And you deserve gear that shows your pride.\" [Product Intro - 10 seconds] \"This [shirt/hoodie/tumbler] was designed BY [identity group] FOR [identity group]. Every detail screams '[identity value]'.\" [Unique Benefit - 8 seconds] \"Plus, it's made from premium [material] that actually lasts. Not that cheap stuff that fades after one wash.\" [Community - 8 seconds] \"Join 10,000+ proud [identity] rocking this design.\" [CTA - 5 seconds] \"Tap to order - ships in 3-5 days.\" Variables to Test: Identity specificity (broad vs narrow niche) Material mention (yes/no) Community size (10k vs 50k) Shipping timeline mention Template 3: Gift-Giving (Seasonal/Holiday POD) Copy [Hook - 3 seconds] \"Need the perfect gift for [dad/mom/best friend]?\" [Struggle - 7 seconds] \"We know finding gifts is stressful. They either have everything or you end up buying something they'll never use.\" [Solution - 10 seconds] \"This [product] is different. It's personal, meaningful, and something they'll actually love. We put [design element] front and center.\" [Emotional Trigger - 10 seconds] \"Imagine their face when they open this. That's the moment we design for.\" [Easy Process - 5 seconds] \"Order in 2 clicks. We handle everything else.\" [CTA - 3 seconds] \"Click to order before [holiday] cutoff!\" Variables to Test: Gift recipient (dad/mom/friend/coworker) Emotional intensity (heartfelt vs funny) Urgency level (cutoff date vs sold out) Price mention (yes/no) Template 4: Social Proof Showcase (Best Seller POD) Copy [Hook - 3 seconds] \"This [product] is EVERYWHERE right now.\" [Social Proof - 8 seconds] \"We've sold 15,000 of these in the last 30 days. It's our #1 best seller and customers are going crazy for it.\" [Why It's Popular - 10 seconds] \"Why? Because it's [unique selling point 1], [USP 2], and [USP 3]. You won't find this anywhere else - we designed it from scratch.\" [Show Reviews - 8 seconds] \"Sarah from Texas said: '[Customer testimonial].' That's what we're talking about.\" [Scarcity - 6 seconds] \"We're restocking weekly but sizes sell out fast.\" [CTA - 3 seconds] \"Grab yours while [size/color] is still available!\" Variables to Test: Social proof numbers (15k vs 50k) Review inclusion (yes/no) Scarcity type (size/color/time) Avatar showing product physically Template 5: Before/After Transformation (Lifestyle POD) Copy [Hook - 3 seconds] \"Before I found this [product], I was [negative state].\" [Before State - 8 seconds] \"I'd settle for basic [product type] that had zero personality. Nothing expressed who I really am.\" [Discovery - 8 seconds] \"Then I discovered [Brand Name]. They get it. This [product] actually represents [value/lifestyle].\" [After State - 10 seconds] \"Now? I get compliments everywhere I go. It's a conversation starter. People ask where I got it.\" [Product Details - 6 seconds] \"Premium quality. Ships fast. Affordable. What's not to love?\" [CTA - 3 seconds] \"Click below to transform your [wardrobe/home/workspace].\" Variables to Test: First-person (I) vs third-person (you) Transformation intensity Brand name mention frequency Lifestyle elements shown in B-roll 🎬 ARCADS VIDEO PRODUCTION CHECKLIST For Each Video: ☐ Script Preparation Hook written (must grab attention in 3 sec) Total length 30-45 seconds CTA clear and specific Read aloud test completed (pacing check) Saved in master script doc with version number ☐ Avatar Selection Matches target demographic (age, gender, vibe) Tested preview clip for authenticity Voice tone selected (friendly/professional/enthusiastic) Avatar ID saved in tracker ☐"}]},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"text":"[Content truncated — view full chat at source URL]"}]},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"text":"Source: "},{"type":"link","href":"https://www.genspark.ai/agents?id=b177cfc6-7e90-432e-b87d-50a1049304f6","children":[{"text":"https://www.genspark.ai/agents?id=b177cfc6-7e90-432e-b87d-50a1049304f6"}]}]}]
